# pos-register does not read from .env at runtime — Flutter config is either
# baked in via --dart-define or received via the register-activation flow
# (tenant_id, workstation_id, api_base_url are handed to the device by the
# admin panel).
#
# This file exists as a placeholder. If you add runtime config that should
# not be committed (local test tokens, personal dev server URLs), put them
# in a real .env and reference via flutter_dotenv — the .gitignore already
# excludes .env / .env.* except this example.
